# notion — credentials (copy to $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/notion/credentials.env,
# default ~/.config/notion/credentials.env, and fill). This is the tier-3
# (user config) source in the 4-tier cascade:
#   flags > project .env(.local) > THIS user config > process env.
# A consuming project can override per-project by setting these in its own .env.
# PUBLIC REPO: never commit real values. Leave blank here; fill only the copy.

# Notion internal-integration token (PAT) — the default identity every call uses.
# Create an integration at https://www.notion.so/my-integrations, then SHARE each
# page/parent it should reach with that integration (Notion access is per-page).
# Never pass it on the command line.
NOTION_TOKEN=

# Alternate identities (optional). The CLI selects which key holds the PAT with
# `--token-env <KEY>` — e.g. to publish as a different integration/workspace. Add
# the key here (or in the project .env) and name it on the call; the value never
# touches the command line. Example:
# NOTION_ALT_TOKEN=
